Title: A Note on the Superstring BRST Operator
Authors: J.N. Acosta, N. Berkovits and O. Chandia (IFT/UNESP, Sao Paulo)
Comments: 4 pages latex
Report-no: IFT-P.021/99
Journal-ref: Phys.Lett. B454 (1999) 247-248
\\
  We write the BRST operator of the N=1 superstring as $Q= e^{-R} (\oint dz
\gamma^2 b)e^R$ where $\gamma$ and $b$ are super-reparameterization ghosts.
This provides a trivial proof that $Q$ is nilpotent.
